Baby and I got to watch @mistyonpointe (thee Misty Copeland) dance as principal in the @abtofficial (American Ballet Theater) last night! Misty Copeland is the first black principal in the history of the company and she was phenomenal. The entire show was beautiful and another reminder about the importance of the arts to economics and culture. I'm looking forward to the day people travel to the Bahamas to see our artists in shows, their songs, their dances, their set and costume designs, their compositions, and of course a thriving middle class to support it. I have a dream y'all and if Misty can do it so can we! #happy #ballet #dance #abt #mistycopeland #newyork #ilovenewyork #theater #thearts #culture #tourism #blackdancer #babybuml #whatmommywore #stylishbump #blackmomsblog  #pregnant #expecting #bumpgoestonewyork #bumpgoestravelling #babybump

Bitter Sweet Symphony

Zenaida Yanowsky's performances in the upcoming run of The Royal Ballet's Symphonic Dances will be among her final roles at the Royal Opera House as a member of the Company.

After 22 years with The Royal Ballet, she announced in December that she will be stepping down as a Principal dancer with the Company in July 2017 at the end of the current Season.

After performing in Marguerite and Armand at Covent Garden in June, Yanowsky's final performance with the Company will be in Australia in July performing Paulina in The Winter’s Tale at the Queensland Performing Arts Centre (@atqpac) as part of The Royal Ballet’s summer visit to Brisbane.
